# Browser check after changes

When you finish a task that edits HTML, CSS, assets, or scripts for this Thought Sweep static site, open the home page in Google Chrome so the user can verify immediately:

`open -a "Google Chrome" "/Users/jakeking/Desktop/TS-Webredesign/index.html"`

Use this path (or the workspace-relative equivalent) after substantive changes. For navigation-only checks of inner pages, opening `index.html` is still acceptable unless the change was isolated to another page—in that case open the edited file (e.g. `demo.html`) in Chrome instead.
